Day 1 - SOC Analyst Level 1

Role of a SOC L1 Analyst:

- Monitor security alerts via SIEM (Security Information and Event Management)
- Analyze alerts based on severity and priority
- Identify false positives vs true positives
- Investigate suspicious activities using available data (logs, users, systems)

Escalation Process:

- If a true positive is confirmed, escalate to SOC L2
- Provide detailed context using the 5W method:
  - WHO: affected user or system
  - WHAT: type of alert or activity
  - WHEN: timestamp of the event
  - WHERE: source/destination
  - WHY: reason for escalation / suspicion
